<p>I have a requirement where I will be downloading my Video file data present on an Azure BLOB. I will get this Video file data in the form of a MemoryStream. </p>  <p>Is there any way that using ffmpeg I can process this MemoryStream e.g removing audio, blurring video etc?</p>  <p>If its not possible then I will have to download the BLOB file somewhere on my Server in the form of .mp4 and then do the processing by ffmpeg. But actually I want to avoid this step of creating file on hard disk downloaded via MemoryStream.</p>  <p>Here is the sample/pseudo code:</p>  <pre><code>public void ProcessVideoFile(string containerName, string blobURI) {     CloudBlockBlob blob = GetBlockBlobReference(containerName, blobURI);      using (var memStream = new MemoryStream())     {         blob.DownloadToStream(memStream);          // Process this memStream using ffmpeg for different filters e.g blurring, remove audio etc.         // ......................     } } </code></pre>